1. Regulation (EC) No 3010/95 shall continue to apply to the tariff concessions for the following products not covered by Annex I or II:
(a) other sugar confectionery containing 70 % or more by weight of sucrose (including invert sugar expressed as sucrose) of subheading ex 1704 90 99;
(b) other food preparations, not containing cocoa powder of subheadings ex 1901 90 91 and ex 1901 90 99.
2. Once the tariff quotas covered by Annex II are exhausted, Regulation (EC) No 3010/95 shall continue to apply to the tariff concessions for the following products:
(a) mixes and doughs for the preparation of bakers' wares of heading No 1905 (subheading 1901 20 00 );
(b) crispbread of subheading 1905 10 00;
(c) bread, not containing added honey, eggs, cheese or fruit, and containing by weight in the dry matter state not more than 5 % of sugars and not more than 5 % of fat of subheading 1905 90 30.
